caption: Facebook pop-up windows are warning that the Department of Homeland Security (acting under a bill known as CISPA) is forwarding entire Facebook histories of Standing Rock protesters to the Federal Bureau of Investigation.

result.explanation: This assessment is knowledge-based. The claim is highly implausible. While CISPA (Cyber Intelligence Sharing and Protection Act) aimed to improve information sharing between private companies and the government, it did not grant the DHS the sweeping power to seize and transmit the entire Facebook histories of protesters to the FBI.  Such an action would represent a massive violation of privacy and would likely face significant legal challenges.  The mention of pop-up windows warning users of this action also adds to its implausibility.  Therefore, this news caption is judged as inaccurate and a likely fabrication.
supporting_evidence: Lack of credible reporting on such a DHS action
CISPA's provisions did not grant such powers
Such action would be a major privacy violation
Implausible use of pop-up windows to deliver such a warning
